Description: Head of terracotta figure of Eros. A head broken from a figure of Eros. His hair is curled on each side of the head and drawn back in parallel plaits at the rear to a central braid running from a topknot above the forehead to a point at the back of the neck. Hollow; two-piece mould. Micaceous brown Nile silt.
Curator's comments: BM Terracotta IV Comparanda. Near: Bayer-Niemeier 1988: no. 539, dated second half of second century ad; Breccia 1934: no. 224, of much better quality.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3370)
